contracts:
  stdout data-only; stderr diagnostics/progress.
  No implicit TUI when automation flags set or stdout non-TTY.
  Color auto off when non-TTY unless forced.
  Use --quiet to silence info logs in robot runs.
  JSON errors only to stderr.
  Swarm status/work-packet/lint are read-only advisory surfaces: they do not claim beads, send mail, reserve files, force-release, run builds, mutate git, or delete data.
  Swarm stale detection is advisory; takeover-like actions require explicit coordination and human/agent confirmation outside cass.
  Swarm evidence defaults are privacy-safe: raw session content and full mail bodies are omitted unless a future explicit redacted evidence opt-in allows snippets.
